allele.allele_interaction:
@shi<up>2</up>@; @&agr;-Adaptin<up>3</up>@/@&agr;-Adaptin@<up>+</up> males are indistinguishable
from wild type at 18<up>o</up>C but at 25<up>o</up>C males can neither fly or walk
and they show sporadic and uncoordinated movements.

Genetic interaction (class, effect): visible | dominant | conditional ts, UI { Chc<up>1</up>/+ }
Genetic interaction (anatomy, effect): wing, UI { Chc<up>1</up>/+ }
Genetic interaction (anatomy, effect): wing vein, UI { Chc<up>1</up>/+ }
Genetic interaction (anatomy, effect): posterior crossvein, UI { Chc<up>1</up>/+ }
Double heterozygotes of @&agr;-Adaptin<up>3</up>@/+ with @Chc<up>1</up>@/+ have a
reduced wing with vein defects at 25<up>o</up>C and the wing remnant phenotype
at 29<up>o</up>C. Double heterozygotes of @&agr;-Adaptin<up>3</up>@/+ with @Chc<up>1</up>@/+
at 18<up>o</up>C show a thickened posterior crossvein phenotype, reminiscent
of the @tkv@ mutant phenotype.

Genetic interaction (effect, class): enhancer | dominant, visible { lqf<up>FDD9</up> }
Genetic interaction (effect, anatomy): enhancer | dominant, eye { lqf<up>FDD9</up> }
Genetic interaction (effect, anatomy): enhancer | dominant, wing { lqf<up>FDD9</up> }
The eye and wing defects of @lqf<up>FDD9</up>@ homozygotes are dominantly
enhanced by @&agr;-Adaptin<up>3</up>@.

Genetic interaction (anatomy, effect): socket | ectopic | somatic clone, non-suppressible { numb<up>hs.PU</up> }
Genetic interaction (anatomy, effect): macrochaeta | somatic clone, non-suppressible { numb<up>hs.PU</up> }
Genetic interaction (effect, anatomy): non-suppressor | somatic clone, macrochaeta | conditional ts { N<up>l1N-ts1</up> }
The bristle transformations seen in @&agr;-Adaptin<up>ear4</up>@ clones are
unaffected by the presence @numb<up>hs.PU</up>@ together with heat shock (2x45
minute 37<up>o</up>C heat shocks separated by 30 minutes, at 16-18 hours APF).
Macrochaetae in somatic clones of @&agr;-Adaptin<up>ear4</up>@ in a @N<up>l1N-ts1</up>@
background at 29<up>o</up>C exhibit a phenotype typical of @N@ (bristle loss),
rather than that seen in @&agr;-Adaptin<up>ear4</up>@ somatic clones in a
wild-type background (transformation to socket cells).

Genetic interaction (effect, class): suppressor { slbo<up>01310</up>, Scer\GAL4<up>slbo.2.6</up> }
Suppresses the sterility and abnormal border follicle cell migration
phenotype of @slbo<up>01310</up>@ females when expressed under the control of
@Scer\GAL4<up>slbo.2.6</up>@.

phenotype.phenotype_desc:
Mutant larvae expressing @&agr;-Adaptin<up>EP896</up>@ under the control of
@Scer\GAL4<up>elav-C155</up>@ have ISN neuron pathfinding defects.
Mutant larvae expressing @&agr;-Adaptin<up>EP896</up>@ under the control of
@Scer\GAL4<up>elav-C155</up>@ have reduced or abnormal synapses.

allele.allele_interaction:
Genetic interaction (anatomy, effect): embryonic/larval tracheal system, UI { shg<up>2</up>/Df(2R)E2, Scer\GAL4<up>btl.PS</up> }
Genetic interaction (anatomy, effect): embryonic/larval dorsal trunk, UI { shg<up>2</up>/Df(2R)E2, Scer\GAL4<up>btl.PS</up> }
@shg<up>2</up>@/@Df(2R)E2@ embryos with @&agr;-Cat<up>Scer\UAS.T:Avic\GFP-sg</up>@
driven by @Scer\GAL4<up>btl.PS</up>@, show largely disordered tracheal branching.
No successful dorsal trunk fusions are seen in these embryos. The
addition of @shg<up>Scer\UAS.cOa</up>@ to these flies rescues these phenotypes
to nearly wild-type. Tracheal patterning is normal, although tracheal
branches and and connectives in the embryos are less extend than in
wild-type.
